-- Czech Republic Leads Serbia 2-0 After First Day of Fed Cup Final
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-11-03T18:03:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-03/czech-republic-leads-serbia-2-0-after-first-day-of-fed-cup-final.html
Lucie Safarova and Petra Kvitova both
won in straight sets to give the  Czech Republic  a 2-0 lead over
Serbia after the opening day of the Fed Cup tennis final.  Safarova beat Ana Ivanovic 6-4, 6-3 in the opening singles
match in Prague. Kvitova then defeated Jelena Jankovic 6-4, 6-1
to move the Czechs within one victory of defending their title.  The best-of-five final in women’s tennis’s top team
competion concludes tomorrow with two reverse singles and a
doubles match.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  